  "body": "Use the local server to serve the following images. There's lots of base64 images being transferred from status-go and kept in memory in nim and qt:\r\n - Community banner\r\n- User profile images (E.g. my profile, demo user profile in Appearance settings)\r\n- Community tokens - The community settings view is always loaded and all the community tokens as well. TODO: use lazy load.\r\n- Community logo\r\n- Profile QR codes\r\n- wallet community tokens. The `Collectibles` view is already a memory bomb because we're missing the means to limit the external collectible image size (we could easily load hundreds of mb for 1 fancy collectible).\r\n\r\n_Originally posted by @alexjba in https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/10339#issuecomment-1864222593_\r\n            ",
